2. Non-.sys extension loading - Loading a valid driver PE using an alternative file extension (e.g. .exe) to evade extension-keyed detections.
3. Service type substitution - Using sc.exe with type=filesys instead of type=kernel to avoid rules that key specifically on the kernel service type string.
4. PE Checksum field mutation - Modifying the PE Checksum header field to alter the raw SHA256 hash while keeping the Authenticode signature valid, defeating hash-based blocklist lookups.
5. WIN_CERTIFICATE structure manipulation - Mutating excluded fields within the WIN_CERTIFICATE structure to shift the file hash without invalidating the digital signature
